A second uprising and fire broke out
at the Sanliurfa prison in southeastern  Turkey , a day after 13
prisoners were killed there, NTV television reported.  Wounded prisoners were being taken to ambulances after
inmates set fire to their beds today, the Istanbul-based
television channel reported.  Thirteen people died at the E-Type jail yesterday after
prisoners protested conditions by setting beds and blankets on
fire, the state-run Anatolia news agency said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
